1
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:33,366
THIS DRAMA IS FICTION
AND THE ELEMENTS OF THE STORY

2
00:00:33,450 --> 00:00:34,576
HAVE NO RELATION TO REALITY.

3
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:35,952
We have high goals.

4
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:37,078
We'll give up Andy.

5
00:00:37,162 --> 00:00:39,539
Let's look at the video
of the foreign players.

6
00:00:39,622 --> 00:00:41,374
Miles? How much is he worth?

7
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:43,668
We're in talks for $500,000.

8
00:00:43,752 --> 00:00:46,421
I'm Robert Gil and I'm here
to serve as a guide.

9
00:00:46,504 --> 00:00:48,298
There hasn't been a time when

10
00:00:48,381 --> 00:00:50,467
a foreign player's contract ended easily,

11
00:00:50,550 --> 00:00:52,218
so I'm a bit worried.

12
00:00:52,302 --> 00:00:53,845
He says the price went up overnight.

13
00:00:53,928 --> 00:00:56,306
Double the price all of a sudden? No way.

14
00:00:56,389 --> 00:00:58,058
That's being too selfish.

15
00:00:58,141 --> 00:01:00,185
We'd be taking Miles at the right price.

16
00:01:00,268 --> 00:01:02,312
Mr. Oh Sa-hoon, do you want to make a bet?

17
00:01:02,395 --> 00:01:03,313
Who's laughing now?

18
00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:05,273
You've got quite the translator.

19
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:07,233
You don't know Gil Chang-ju?

20
00:01:07,317 --> 00:01:08,902
Robert Gil is Gil Chang-ju.

21
00:01:08,985 --> 00:01:11,279
I'm legally American now.

22
00:01:11,362 --> 00:01:13,782
If you think about going back to Korea...

23
00:01:13,865 --> 00:01:16,242
Who would recruit a player like me?

24
00:01:16,326 --> 00:01:18,703
People see me as the guy who
evaded military service.

25
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:20,538
This is just wrong!

26
00:01:20,622 --> 00:01:22,373
Are you to be blamed the whole season?

27
00:01:22,457 --> 00:01:24,042
Do you think we can sign

28
00:01:24,125 --> 00:01:25,794
a better foreign player for $500,000?

29
00:01:25,877 --> 00:01:27,504
I couldn't see the problem,

30
00:01:27,587 --> 00:01:29,130
so I requested it be discharged.

31
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:30,423
Mr. Gil.

32
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:33,093
Do you really not have any reason
to be desperate?

33
00:01:33,176 --> 00:01:35,011
I can play baseball again.

34
00:01:35,095 --> 00:01:38,306
I told you I could bet
that we would be the ones to smile first.

35
00:01:38,389 --> 00:01:39,432
Chin up.

36
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:41,351
This is not even a big deal.

37
00:01:41,851 --> 00:01:42,852
Let's go.

38
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:50,485
PRESS CONFERENCE 2019

39
00:01:51,736 --> 00:01:54,239
I'm Reporter Kim Jung-gu
of Financial Modern.

40
00:01:54,322 --> 00:01:56,825
Let me make my question
short and straight to the point.

41
00:01:57,158 --> 00:01:58,368
Why is it Gil Chang-ju?

42
00:01:59,202 --> 00:02:00,286
Well,

43
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:02,789
he can throw a strong fastball
to wherever he wants.

44
00:02:02,872 --> 00:02:04,666
That's the kind of player he is.

45
00:02:04,749 --> 00:02:06,668
Did you consider
what the people would think?

46
00:02:06,751 --> 00:02:10,130
We brought the best player
we could choose,

47
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:12,465
although his past isn't so ideal.

48
00:02:12,549 --> 00:02:14,217
I'm Jung Soon-geun of Jungdong Daily.

49
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:17,720
Mr. Gil became an American citizen
to avoid military duty.

50
00:02:18,012 --> 00:02:20,348
If he gets to play baseball again
in this country,

51
00:02:20,431 --> 00:02:22,433
other Korean men will
most likely feel deprived.

52
00:02:22,517 --> 00:02:24,018
What will you do about it?

53
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:30,692
Jungdong Daily?

54
00:02:31,985 --> 00:02:35,947
I won't deny that Mr. Gil played
a role in that sense of deprivation.

55
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,699
I'm aware of it,

56
00:02:37,866 --> 00:02:40,034
and he's aware of it, too.

57
00:02:40,743 --> 00:02:43,246
Right, he will have to bear criticism

58
00:02:43,329 --> 00:02:45,039
that's much harsher than other people,

59
00:02:45,123 --> 00:02:46,833
like the sons of media owners
or politicians

60
00:02:47,917 --> 00:02:49,794
who were exempted from military duty

61
00:02:49,878 --> 00:02:52,130
for excuses like essential hypertension.

62
00:02:54,215 --> 00:02:55,300
But you know what?

63
00:02:55,758 --> 00:02:58,595
There was a young baseball player
with a promising future.

64
00:02:58,803 --> 00:03:01,389
He was selected as the ace player
of the national youth team.

65
00:03:01,472 --> 00:03:04,809
He played in a total of four games,
including two preliminaries.

66
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:09,856
He was the winning pitcher
for the semi-finals, and for the finals,

67
00:03:09,939 --> 00:03:10,982
he was the relief pitcher.

68
00:03:11,065 --> 00:03:12,400
His team won the championship,

69
00:03:12,483 --> 00:03:14,694
but unfortunately, he injured his elbow.

70
00:03:14,777 --> 00:03:18,198
He went to the States for surgery
and focused on rehab.

71
00:03:18,656 --> 00:03:20,241
After the rehab,

72
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:21,701
his results came out.

73
00:03:21,784 --> 00:03:22,744
NINE WINS THIS SEASON

74
00:03:22,827 --> 00:03:24,370
Then he finally got recognized.

75
00:03:25,788 --> 00:03:26,789
However,

76
00:03:27,457 --> 00:03:29,626
he was faced with the time
to serve in the army

77
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:33,546
when he became a promising rookie
in the Major League.

78
00:03:36,007 --> 00:03:38,134
Around that time, there was a survey

79
00:03:38,468 --> 00:03:41,846
for which 70 percent of the answers
favored naturalization.

80
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:45,308
Are you saying
his naturalization was just?

81
00:03:45,683 --> 00:03:47,769
I do not think it was just,

82
00:03:47,852 --> 00:03:49,729
and that is why
I'm making it a long story.

83
00:03:49,812 --> 00:03:50,772
-What?
-Goodness.

84
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,947
Can I ask you one last question?

85
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:04,452
I'm Kim Young-chae of Baseball Is Life.

86
00:04:05,828 --> 00:04:08,790
There might be a way
for him to be forgiven.

87
00:04:11,834 --> 00:04:13,962
What do you think about him

88
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:15,672
serving in the army now?

89
00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:29,560
Due to time constraints,
we'll end the press conference here.

90
00:04:29,852 --> 00:04:31,020
You may get up.

91
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:34,857
-Hey.
-Please answer.

92
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:36,150
Please answer the question.

93
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:41,030
If you end it now, it seems like
you're running away.

94
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:42,991
You're right. We're running away.

95
00:04:43,074 --> 00:04:45,660
You have to face them head on.
We all came here determined.

96
00:04:45,743 --> 00:04:47,787
I don't know how to fight
with my hands tied.

97
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:49,247
We fight when we know how to win.

98
00:04:49,330 --> 00:04:51,291
I have something I'd like to say.

99
00:04:51,374 --> 00:04:52,792
Say it later. Let's go.

100
00:04:59,257 --> 00:05:01,050
AMERICAN GIL CHANG-JU COMES BACK

101
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:02,969
Will the Dreams rise back up?

102
00:05:04,804 --> 00:05:07,015
I said we'd be willing
to pay up to $900,000.

103
00:05:07,098 --> 00:05:08,808
Yes, you did.

104
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:12,729
But they used only 500,000
and brought a lousy one?

105
00:05:13,688 --> 00:05:14,772
But...

106
00:05:14,897 --> 00:05:17,483
he's played in the Major League.

107
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:20,737
If he were that great,
why would he come for only 500,000?

108
00:05:21,362 --> 00:05:23,114
His price represents his skills.

109
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:24,991
Yes, that's true.

110
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,452
Then, when Baek Seung-soo comes,

111
00:05:28,161 --> 00:05:30,288
do I have to compliment him

112
00:05:30,371 --> 00:05:31,331
or scold him?

113
00:05:31,414 --> 00:05:35,293
I think we need to see first
how the public opinion is.

114
00:05:35,376 --> 00:05:37,128
No, I think

115
00:05:37,837 --> 00:05:41,007
I should compliment him
for showing some clueless courage.

116
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:43,885
Baek Seung-soo.

117
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:46,679
He's a bit...

118
00:05:48,723 --> 00:05:50,725
strange, isn't he?

119
00:05:51,517 --> 00:05:54,979
Aware of the controversy
surrounding Gil Chang-ju avoiding

120
00:05:55,063 --> 00:05:57,690
his military service,
the Dreams held a press conference.

121
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:02,362
General Manager Baek Seung-soo showed
his conviction regarding the player.

122
00:06:06,449 --> 00:06:08,910
-You're home.
-Yes. How have you been?

123
00:06:10,411 --> 00:06:11,829
Did you not eat yet?

124
00:06:11,913 --> 00:06:15,041
You must be tired.
I'll prepare the food today.

125
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:17,377
Thanks.

126
00:06:23,841 --> 00:06:24,967
Gosh.

127
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:28,763
While I prepare the food, you should relax

128
00:06:28,846 --> 00:06:31,349
and take out the presents.

129
00:06:32,141 --> 00:06:35,061
It doesn't have to be
anything heartfelt or serious.

130
00:06:35,144 --> 00:06:37,397
It just has to be expensive.

131
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:01,504
HIGH SCHOOL

132
00:07:12,014 --> 00:07:13,099
Seung-soo, let's eat.

133
00:07:16,394 --> 00:07:17,228
Okay.

134
00:07:27,071 --> 00:07:29,991
I didn't crave any Korean food
when I was away,

135
00:07:30,074 --> 00:07:32,535
so I thought I was very American
in that sense.

136
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:35,955
But I was wrong.
I was forgetting this taste.

137
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:37,832
How dirty.

138
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:39,542
Talk after eating.

139
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:42,587
I might be on TV tomorrow.
Can you take out a beauty mask?

140
00:07:42,670 --> 00:07:46,549
No one would notice even if you had
five watermelon seeds on your face.

141
00:07:47,216 --> 00:07:48,676
Do you have to say it like that?

142
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:51,345
Hey, are you sure
you brought the right person?

143
00:07:51,429 --> 00:07:53,014
There's a lot of controversy.

144
00:07:53,097 --> 00:07:55,308
He's a good person
who takes responsibility.

145
00:07:55,391 --> 00:07:57,768
-If he had responsibility--
-Mom.

146
00:07:57,852 --> 00:08:01,355
We should stand by his side, at least.

147
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:03,524
And apart from that,

148
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:06,068
he has a strong sense
of responsibility for his family.

149
00:08:06,736 --> 00:08:09,530
That's why he worked
as a coordinator to earn money.

150
00:08:09,614 --> 00:08:11,532
At night, he'd train.

151
00:08:11,616 --> 00:08:12,992
He'll do well.

152
00:08:14,118 --> 00:08:14,994
How would you know?

153
00:08:15,077 --> 00:08:16,787
That's how your dad was.

154
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:19,081
After he knew you were in my belly,

155
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:21,167
he brought home the most money
he ever did. Here.

156
00:08:25,421 --> 00:08:29,091
Before I was born,
Dad was too much of a playboy.

157
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:32,887
But when he has
a heavy burden on his shoulders,

158
00:08:32,970 --> 00:08:34,722
you have to believe and be at ease.

159
00:08:35,681 --> 00:08:37,183
Even if he doesn't play well,

160
00:08:37,266 --> 00:08:38,851
don't blame him too much.

161
00:08:38,935 --> 00:08:40,686
Don't feel sympathy for him!

162
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:42,647
He gets paid way more than me!

163
00:08:42,730 --> 00:08:43,564
Way more!

164
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:46,067
It's because you get paid too little!

165
00:08:47,735 --> 00:08:49,737
There you go again talking about my pay.

166
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:56,327
ROBERT GIL

167
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:02,208
Sir.

168
00:09:03,042 --> 00:09:03,918
Look who's here.

169
00:09:05,836 --> 00:09:08,548
Didn't we have more journalists
expected to come?

170
00:09:10,258 --> 00:09:12,218
Just looking at the press conference,

171
00:09:12,301 --> 00:09:14,887
it didn't seem like he'd answer
any tough questions.

172
00:09:14,971 --> 00:09:17,723
I guess the journalists
weren't feeling it either.

173
00:09:18,975 --> 00:09:19,934
Let's wait.

174
00:09:20,017 --> 00:09:22,311
-Wait for what?
-Our hidden card.

175
00:09:27,191 --> 00:09:29,193
Hello!

176
00:09:31,404 --> 00:09:33,114
Hello!

177
00:09:33,656 --> 00:09:35,241
-Hello.
-Have you been well?

178
00:09:35,324 --> 00:09:36,450
Yes.

179
00:09:36,742 --> 00:09:39,161
This is our operations manager.

180
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:41,497
I know of Ms. Lee Se-young.

181
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:43,541
We met at the conference
and before that as well.

182
00:09:43,624 --> 00:09:44,584
How did you know her?

183
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:47,128
If I didn't know the first female
operations manager

184
00:09:47,211 --> 00:09:49,380
in our country, I should quit
my job. Am I wrong?

185
00:09:51,632 --> 00:09:54,135
But at the press conference,

186
00:09:55,469 --> 00:09:56,887
you were too mean.

187
00:09:57,722 --> 00:09:58,556
I was?

188
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:03,144
I only asked a question
that everyone was curious about.

189
00:10:03,227 --> 00:10:07,857
If you were considerate of Gil Chang-ju,

190
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:11,902
you wouldn't have asked that question
as soon as he returned to Korea.

191
00:10:14,739 --> 00:10:18,159
-Hello, everyone.
-Hello, sir.

192
00:10:18,242 --> 00:10:19,785
Hello, everyone.

193
00:10:21,162 --> 00:10:22,204
Hello, sir.

194
00:10:23,664 --> 00:10:24,999
-Excuse me.
-Yes.

195
00:10:25,082 --> 00:10:26,542
Is it hard to get an interview?

196
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:29,045
Do you think I would have
asked only once or twice

197
00:10:29,128 --> 00:10:31,172
when it was you who wants the interview?

198
00:10:32,381 --> 00:10:34,759
-He says he doesn't want to.
-Then I'll ask myself,

199
00:10:34,842 --> 00:10:36,594
-face to face.
-What?

200
00:10:41,891 --> 00:10:44,226
Hello, Mr. Baek. I'm Kim Young-chae.

201
00:10:44,977 --> 00:10:46,395
Yes. Hello.

202
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:49,065
Confirm with the strategy analysis team
if their cameras are ready.

203
00:10:49,148 --> 00:10:50,316
Yes, sir.

204
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:53,778
-A hidden card?
-Yes, a hidden card.

205
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:57,073
I have a lot of questions.

206
00:10:57,156 --> 00:10:58,991
You can go through the PR team.

207
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:01,035
So you can reject it through the PR team?

208
00:11:01,118 --> 00:11:02,036
Yes.

209
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:08,542
The Dreams is the club that's
preparing for the biggest changes.

210
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:11,921
Is there a reason
you're not replacing the manager?

211
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:15,383
It must be similar to the reason
the producer isn't replacing you.

212
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:22,306
I appreciate your kind words.

213
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:25,351
I'll officially be rejected
through the PR team.

214
00:11:44,203 --> 00:11:46,831
-I'm nervous.
-Are they paying you more

215
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:49,625
-for pitching better balls?
-Mr. Baek said

216
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:54,672
that everyone will be convinced why
he brought me as the season begins.

217
00:11:55,297 --> 00:11:56,340
But...

218
00:11:56,841 --> 00:11:59,009
I'd like to convince them right now.

219
00:11:59,719 --> 00:12:03,723
I don't think I should let him be
criticized because of me anymore.

220
00:12:04,432 --> 00:12:07,268
May I throw the ball
with maximum strength?

221
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:10,146
Do you think any team would keep us
in check or analyze us

222
00:12:10,521 --> 00:12:13,399
just because you're pitching
a little bit better?

223
00:12:13,482 --> 00:12:14,817
Just pitch as you always do.

224
00:12:38,132 --> 00:12:39,425
Mr. Gil Chang-ju,

225
00:12:39,508 --> 00:12:43,053
please tell us how you feel
about your return to Korea.

226
00:12:43,137 --> 00:12:46,265
For letting me stand on this mound,

227
00:12:46,348 --> 00:12:48,267
for all the reporters

228
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:50,978
paying attention to me,

229
00:12:51,228 --> 00:12:55,107
and for calling me Gil Chang-ju,
not Robert Gil,

230
00:12:55,191 --> 00:12:56,525
I appreciate it all.

231
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:57,902
Yes.

232
00:12:57,985 --> 00:13:01,530
You've just shown us
some good pitches.

233
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:05,993
It feels like I'm sparing words
of praise by saying "good."

234
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:10,998
I'll say it directly.
Those were very powerful pitches.

235
00:13:11,081 --> 00:13:12,458
Thank you.

236
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,293
Before that,

237
00:13:15,252 --> 00:13:17,338
I'd like to apologize first.

238
00:13:18,380 --> 00:13:22,343
There is no excuse for the fact that
I've let down many baseball fans.

239
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:25,930
And I'll accept any criticism
on that matter.

240
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:29,016
I sincerely apologize again.

241
00:13:30,601 --> 00:13:33,687
Let's wrap it up. Good work, everyone.

242
00:13:38,609 --> 00:13:39,610
Hey.

243
00:13:46,659 --> 00:13:48,994
Hey. I constantly search my name

244
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:52,873
and the name of our group
just like those kids nowadays.

245
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:55,960
-And what is going on?
-Well, sir...

246
00:13:56,043 --> 00:13:58,754
The firm's name keeps coming up
in the sports section.

247
00:14:00,422 --> 00:14:01,340
What do we do?

248
00:14:02,174 --> 00:14:03,551
I apologize.

249
00:14:03,717 --> 00:14:05,386
Why are they making a fuss

250
00:14:05,469 --> 00:14:07,263
for something useless and of no profit?

251
00:14:07,888 --> 00:14:09,056
I apologize.

252
00:14:10,474 --> 00:14:12,268
Did you bring a troublemaker from the US?

253
00:14:13,853 --> 00:14:15,938
Yes, the general manager has been

254
00:14:16,021 --> 00:14:18,482
causing a bit of trouble recently.

255
00:14:18,858 --> 00:14:20,818
But it's all part of the plan.

256
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:23,320
On a larger scale,
it's going as you have wished.

257
00:14:23,404 --> 00:14:24,238
Kyung-min.

258
00:14:24,905 --> 00:14:25,739
Yes, sir.

259
00:14:25,823 --> 00:14:28,242
You're good at your job
because we're related by blood.

260
00:14:28,325 --> 00:14:29,535
