00:29:33,062 --> 00:29:34,731
Are you referring to the domestic league?

523
00:29:35,482 --> 00:29:37,233
It's different depending on the index.

524
00:29:37,317 --> 00:29:39,235
Right, you know.

525
00:29:39,319 --> 00:29:42,322
It changes according to which
analytical technique you use,

526
00:29:42,405 --> 00:29:45,241
but as far as I know,
about 200 at-bats for strikeouts,

527
00:29:45,617 --> 00:29:47,118
400 at-bats for walks,

528
00:29:47,202 --> 00:29:48,453
and 300 at-bats for SLG.

529
00:29:48,536 --> 00:29:49,829
HITTER'S BATTING PRODUCTIVITY

530
00:29:49,913 --> 00:29:53,082
Then in terms of the Major League,
the sample should be...

531
00:29:53,166 --> 00:29:55,502
As far as I know,
fewer samples are needed.

532
00:29:55,585 --> 00:29:57,587
-Why is that?
-Well...

533
00:29:59,130 --> 00:30:00,465
I'm not sure.

534
00:30:00,548 --> 00:30:02,133
WAITING ROOM

535
00:30:13,436 --> 00:30:15,855
Think of it as an experience
even if you fail.

536
00:30:15,980 --> 00:30:17,398
You've studied hard.

537
00:30:22,654 --> 00:30:24,989
What's the answer
to your question from earlier?

538
00:30:26,199 --> 00:30:28,409
There's no definite answer to it.

539
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:30,537
I just wanted to see him
interpret the statistics.

540
00:30:31,913 --> 00:30:32,747
Where did you learn

541
00:30:33,373 --> 00:30:34,332
things like that?

542
00:30:34,415 --> 00:30:35,792
I read books.

543
00:30:35,875 --> 00:30:38,211
I also often check Yamanse for reference.

544
00:30:42,549 --> 00:30:44,092
RESUME

545
00:30:50,849 --> 00:30:53,059
It's okay. I'll try it on my own.

546
00:31:38,187 --> 00:31:39,522
Hello.

547
00:31:40,356 --> 00:31:41,482
Hello.

548
00:31:42,233 --> 00:31:43,610
Shall we begin the interview?

549
00:31:45,236 --> 00:31:47,155
BAEK YOUNG-SOO

550
00:31:47,238 --> 00:31:48,865
I'll deliver it for you.

551
00:31:48,948 --> 00:31:50,408
Thank you.

552
00:31:56,998 --> 00:31:58,666
THE HEAT CHANGES EVERYTHING

553
00:31:58,750 --> 00:31:59,792
Gosh.

554
00:32:01,002 --> 00:32:05,214
Are you Robinson of Yamanse?

555
00:32:06,549 --> 00:32:09,052
You wrote "The Heat Changes
Everything, Even Baseball"

556
00:32:09,135 --> 00:32:12,221
and the post
about the Pythagorean winning data.

557
00:32:12,305 --> 00:32:13,306
Right?

558
00:32:15,016 --> 00:32:16,225
You don't know him?

559
00:32:17,310 --> 00:32:18,144
I don't.

560
00:32:18,227 --> 00:32:20,772
Oh, I see. He's really famous.

561
00:32:21,981 --> 00:32:27,111
I'm Baek Young-soo and I often post
on Yamanse using my ID Robinson.

562
00:32:28,154 --> 00:32:29,822
I chose a few articles

563
00:32:30,114 --> 00:32:32,200
about the team performance analysis

564
00:32:32,283 --> 00:32:35,328
from the things I've written so far.

565
00:32:36,329 --> 00:32:37,622
You wrote a lot.

566
00:32:38,331 --> 00:32:39,332
By the way,

567
00:32:39,791 --> 00:32:42,085
is this really helpful
for the team performance?

568
00:32:43,294 --> 00:32:45,338
You must be the strategy
analysis team leader.

569
00:32:46,297 --> 00:32:47,799
-You're right.
-I'm sure

570
00:32:47,882 --> 00:32:50,677
you already apply sabermetrics
when analyzing the statistics.

571
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:53,638
You make and gather the detailed
stats of each player, right?

572
00:32:53,888 --> 00:32:57,016
But you make different choices
based on how you interpret data.

573
00:32:57,100 --> 00:32:59,978
You would know it well
if you've ever played baseball.

574
00:33:00,395 --> 00:33:04,440
There are so many reasons
people don't see beyond the numbers.

575
00:33:04,524 --> 00:33:07,568
Most players that hit a slump
all of a sudden

576
00:33:07,652 --> 00:33:10,863
turn out to have personal issues
with their girlfriend or family.

577
00:33:10,947 --> 00:33:14,534
But sabermetrics has no clue
about such issues, right?

578
00:33:14,617 --> 00:33:16,494
Among all the sports,

579
00:33:16,577 --> 00:33:19,497
I think baseball is the best one
to be analyzed by numbers.

580
00:33:20,331 --> 00:33:22,375
In basketball, volleyball, and football,

581
00:33:22,458 --> 00:33:26,587
all the plays are easily
affected by other players' moves.

582
00:33:26,671 --> 00:33:30,341
But for baseball,
players can make strikeouts and hits

583
00:33:30,425 --> 00:33:32,343
without the help of other players.

584
00:33:33,553 --> 00:33:36,764
Not introducing sabermetrics
in modern baseball

585
00:33:37,056 --> 00:33:40,768
is the same as not willing to be healthy.

586
00:33:41,686 --> 00:33:44,772
Even if you study sabermetrics,
you don't get an official diploma.

587
00:33:44,856 --> 00:33:47,066
So if you're not getting a job
in this field,

588
00:33:47,150 --> 00:33:49,402
you'd feel there is too much to study.

589
00:33:50,653 --> 00:33:52,238
Seung-soo, what are you doing?

590
00:33:52,363 --> 00:33:53,656
If I...

591
00:33:54,949 --> 00:33:56,492
quit baseball,

592
00:33:56,826 --> 00:33:59,037
can you teach me how to study?

593
00:34:00,329 --> 00:34:01,497
Young-soo.

594
00:34:02,457 --> 00:34:05,126
You're talented in baseball
more than any other thing.

595
00:34:05,209 --> 00:34:06,544
You're not smart that way.

596
00:34:07,962 --> 00:34:11,758
-Hello? Young-soo, I need to go.
-Seung-soo,

597
00:34:11,841 --> 00:34:13,760
I have a game today.

598
00:34:13,843 --> 00:34:15,136
Yes. And what?

599
00:34:15,845 --> 00:34:18,097
And my pelvis has been hurting
since yesterday.

600
00:34:18,181 --> 00:34:20,516
I heard that suffering from pain
is inevitable

601
00:34:21,267 --> 00:34:24,562
for all players as they use
explosive energy at once.

602
00:34:25,521 --> 00:34:28,858
Young-soo, don't look back
and look forward.

603
00:34:29,025 --> 00:34:30,943
Just go forward, okay?

604
00:34:31,944 --> 00:34:34,655
Tell me how many hits you got
after the game.

605
00:34:37,408 --> 00:34:40,161
To my knowledge, even the Sabers,

606
00:34:40,244 --> 00:34:44,791
the champion of last season,
didn't fully adopt sabermetrics.

607
00:34:44,874 --> 00:34:46,209
Many think the same as you

608
00:34:46,292 --> 00:34:49,670
because the Sabers didn't hire
regular workers for stat analysis.

609
00:34:49,754 --> 00:34:50,630
But as far as I know,

610
00:34:50,713 --> 00:34:54,092
they have two contract workers
designated for the task,

611
00:34:54,175 --> 00:34:55,176
and the two refused

612
00:34:55,259 --> 00:34:57,678
to work as regular workers for the team.

613
00:34:57,929 --> 00:35:00,056
And their wages were raised
a lot recently.

614
00:35:00,139 --> 00:35:02,934
Do you think those who studied
the mere numbers

615
00:35:03,017 --> 00:35:06,687
can work for baseball teams
even if they have

616
00:35:07,271 --> 00:35:08,689
not made a strikeout or hit a homer?

617
00:35:08,773 --> 00:35:10,942
I've made strikeouts and hit homers.

618
00:35:11,526 --> 00:35:12,652
Not your neighborhood league.

619
00:35:12,735 --> 00:35:14,654
No, not in my neighborhood league.

620
00:35:17,448 --> 00:35:18,282
DAESUNG HIGH SCHOOL

621
00:35:18,366 --> 00:35:19,367
Daesung High School?

622
00:35:19,450 --> 00:35:20,827
Yes. Also, I believe

623
00:35:20,910 --> 00:35:25,206
if there's anyone who hasn't
made a home run or a strikeout

624
00:35:25,289 --> 00:35:27,792
but knows sabermetrics better than me,

625
00:35:27,875 --> 00:35:29,460
he should be hired instead of me.

626
00:35:30,878 --> 00:35:32,296
You're very confident.

627
00:35:32,505 --> 00:35:34,298
Of course, the analytical skills
are not always

628
00:35:34,382 --> 00:35:36,300
directly related to the team's standing.

629
00:35:36,384 --> 00:35:39,637
There are also many other factors
that determine the standing.

630
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:43,599
However, for the Dreams,
who have neglected statistics,

631
00:35:43,683 --> 00:35:46,602
I'm sure it can give
some substantial help.

632
00:35:46,853 --> 00:35:49,272
WAR is regarded
as one of the most important statistics

633
00:35:49,355 --> 00:35:52,525
when it comes to sabermetrics.

634
00:35:52,692 --> 00:35:56,487
Can you tell me why hitters usually
show higher WAR than pitchers,

635
00:35:56,571 --> 00:35:59,407
while many say pitchers matter
the most in baseball?

636
00:35:59,490 --> 00:36:00,366
That's the point.

637
00:36:00,449 --> 00:36:04,036
That's the reason why we don't
trust these numbers in the field.

638
00:36:04,120 --> 00:36:07,331
The first reason is that hitters
do both hitting and defense

639
00:36:07,415 --> 00:36:08,875
at the same time.

640
00:36:08,958 --> 00:36:11,669
So, the starting pitchers' WAR
is not much lower

641
00:36:11,752 --> 00:36:12,962
than the hitters.

642
00:36:13,045 --> 00:36:17,550
But middle relief pitchers
have really low WAR.

643
00:36:17,633 --> 00:36:21,220
But aren't their roles
really important to win games?

644
00:36:21,304 --> 00:36:23,181
Right. So I think we should use

645
00:36:23,264 --> 00:36:26,225
WPA, the win probability added,
instead of WAR

646
00:36:26,309 --> 00:36:29,520
to evaluate the performance
of middle relief pitchers

647
00:36:29,604 --> 00:36:31,689
in a more accurate way.

648
00:36:38,196 --> 00:36:39,864
You don't have any questions to ask?

649
00:36:46,412 --> 00:36:48,831
How high do you think the doorsill is?

650
00:36:51,459 --> 00:36:54,212
The doorsill you just crossed.

651
00:36:54,337 --> 00:36:55,713
The doorsill...

652
00:36:57,006 --> 00:37:01,844
you barely managed to cross
with someone else's help in the end.

653
00:37:03,429 --> 00:37:05,264
I think it'd be
about six centimeters high.

654
00:37:05,348 --> 00:37:08,059
Everything,
including such a trivial thing,

655
00:37:08,893 --> 00:37:10,603
would be tough if you work for us.

656
00:37:11,771 --> 00:37:12,605
Mr. Baek.

657
00:37:12,688 --> 00:37:17,068
He should understand it exactly first
to accept whatever decision we'd make.

658
00:37:21,280 --> 00:37:24,450
I really like Jackie Robinson.

659
00:37:25,868 --> 00:37:28,204
That's why my ID is Robinson.

660
00:37:29,914 --> 00:37:32,667
He's the first African American
player in MLB.

661
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:36,003
He had to fight against
the unfair calls of umpires,

662
00:37:36,295 --> 00:37:40,466
and many pitchers hit him on purpose
just because he was African American.

663
00:37:42,176 --> 00:37:44,011
It's total nonsense in this day and age.

664
00:37:44,095 --> 00:37:48,224
If you hire me, I'd be
the first disabled baseball analyst.

665
00:37:48,891 --> 00:37:51,727
The press would eagerly
write stories about me.

666
00:37:51,811 --> 00:37:53,729
Such stories aren't what we are after--

667
00:37:53,813 --> 00:37:56,148
I want you to know this.

668
00:37:56,857 --> 00:37:58,567
If you don't hear good news from us,

669
00:37:59,193 --> 00:38:02,238
that means we found someone
more competent than you.

670
00:38:03,656 --> 00:38:06,784
We won't give you a disadvantage
because you are different.

671
00:38:08,286 --> 00:38:09,287
I trust you.

672
00:38:11,372 --> 00:38:14,709
-Let me ask one more question...
-You got injured.

673
00:38:18,504 --> 00:38:19,922
Tell us what happened.

674
00:38:21,966 --> 00:38:23,050
Sorry?

675
00:38:43,738 --> 00:38:44,739
Young-soo,

676
00:38:44,905 --> 00:38:47,241
don't look back and look forward.

677
00:38:47,533 --> 00:38:49,952
Just go forward, okay?

678
00:39:15,853 --> 00:39:17,521
I got injured during a baseball game.

679
00:39:22,401 --> 00:39:26,906
You'll have to watch
countless game recordings.

680
00:39:28,574 --> 00:39:30,117
The recordings of real games.

681
00:39:32,620 --> 00:39:35,581
You might think you'd still be
in the field if that didn't happen.

682
00:39:36,374 --> 00:39:37,833
Also, you must easily recall

683
00:39:39,877 --> 00:39:42,296
the moment you crashed
and all the ugly memories.

684
00:39:44,006 --> 00:39:45,174
Can you handle it?

685
00:39:48,010 --> 00:39:48,844
I can.

686
00:39:48,928 --> 00:39:52,807
Would your family also want that?

687
00:39:57,061 --> 00:39:58,312
My family doesn't know.

688
00:40:00,773 --> 00:40:02,024
This is what I want.

689
00:40:05,611 --> 00:40:07,154
And that's why I'm doing this.

690
00:40:08,531 --> 00:40:09,949
Because I'm fine.

691
00:40:36,684 --> 00:40:39,019
Applicant Baek Young-soo
is my younger brother.

692
00:40:40,813 --> 00:40:44,692
I wasn't aware he applied,
nor do I hope for his employment.

693
00:40:44,775 --> 00:40:47,653
Please judge it
as objectively as possible.

694
00:40:48,529 --> 00:40:49,697
But I don't think...

695
00:40:51,615 --> 00:40:53,576
you have judged it objectively.

696
00:40:53,659 --> 00:40:56,996
He must have considered how I would
rate him before he came here.

697
00:41:02,877 --> 00:41:04,253
Even though it's your brother,

698
00:41:05,838 --> 00:41:07,882
you crossed the line earlier.

699
00:41:08,799 --> 00:41:10,801
Even though he could guess

700
00:41:11,719 --> 00:41:13,095
why you would talk to him that way.

701
00:41:24,982 --> 00:41:26,859
We have no choice.

702
00:41:26,942 --> 00:41:28,903
I'll just announce the result
based on the scores.

703
00:41:28,986 --> 00:41:30,821
Why? What did he say?

704
00:41:30,905 --> 00:41:32,364
Shush.

705
00:41:42,666 --> 00:41:43,501
BAEK YOUNG-SOO

706
00:41:45,961 --> 00:41:47,463
BAEK YOUNG-SOO, DAESUNG HIGH

707
00:41:47,546 --> 00:41:50,674
The intense advance that ended
the career of a rising star.

708
00:41:52,593 --> 00:41:54,428
There has been a sad accident
during the match

709
00:41:58,307 --> 00:42:00,351
Tolerating an injury led to severe injury.

710
00:42:00,434 --> 00:42:01,977
I hope no more incidents like that

711
00:42:14,406 --> 00:42:15,783
Mr. Baek!

712
00:42:16,075 --> 00:42:17,159
Hold on.

713
00:42:20,162 --> 00:42:22,248
I checked the heights
of the doorsills in our office.

714
00:42:22,957 --> 00:42:25,209
We have eight doors with thresholds
of less than 2cm,

715
00:42:25,292 --> 00:42:26,710
or don't have one.

716
00:42:26,835 --> 00:42:28,963
He can pass these doors in the wheelchair.

717
00:42:29,547 --> 00:42:32,925
We can also install ramps
on the doors with higher thresholds.

718
00:42:33,467 --> 00:42:36,053
We can solve the problem
with a much cheaper budget

719
00:42:36,136 --> 00:42:37,263
than installing new doors.

720
00:42:38,597 --> 00:42:39,557
I still won't hire him.

721
00:42:40,224 --> 00:42:43,686
We have to hire someone
who can assist and protect you.

722
00:42:45,604 --> 00:42:47,398
Who would assist whom?

723
00:42:47,690 --> 00:42:50,401
Please just do as much work
as others in your position.

724
00:42:51,819 --> 00:42:53,654
Who's protecting whom?

725
00:43:05,291 --> 00:43:06,792
What are you doing?

726
00:43:07,585 --> 00:43:10,296
You always say your piece and just leave.

727
00:43:13,507 --> 00:43:15,175
Fine. Say what you want.

728
00:43:19,179 --> 00:43:22,975
Your brother was a good player.

729
00:43:27,563 --> 00:43:28,939
That past doesn't exist.

730
00:43:30,858 --> 00:43:31,817
RESUME

731
00:43:31,900 --> 00:43:34,612
Have you read his resume thoroughly?

732
00:43:35,863 --> 00:43:38,407
Do you think we're close enough
to talk about these things?

733
00:43:38,490 --> 00:43:40,701
I'd like to stop talking about my family.

734
00:43:40,784 --> 00:43:45,956
I'm talking about hiring an employee
of the strategy analysis team right now.

735
00:43:47,416 --> 00:43:49,126
You made me realize

736
00:43:49,460 --> 00:43:52,338
that you don't know all about him
even though you two are close.

737
00:43:59,678 --> 00:44:00,721
RESUME

738
00:44:00,804 --> 00:44:03,891
It doesn't say anything about him
going through a hard time, does it?

739
00:44:07,019 --> 00:44:08,354
But you can tell.

740
00:44:08,437 --> 00:44:11,398
With that one line where it says
he majored in statistics,

741
00:44:12,274 --> 00:44:13,651
he deserves to be applauded.

742
00:44:13,734 --> 00:44:17,237
No company hires an employee
because of a line in their resume.

743
00:44:17,321 --> 00:44:21,116
You're working in the sport
that got your brother injured.

744
00:44:21,533 --> 00:44:23,243
You must not have come here

745
00:44:23,327 --> 00:44:25,954
without determination or hesitation.

746
00:44:26,914 --> 00:44:27,873
But...

747
00:44:29,291 --> 00:44:32,127
don't you think your brother would have

748
00:44:32,211 --> 00:44:34,338
made a tougher decision

749
00:44:34,880 --> 00:44:36,882
than the decision you had to make?

750
00:44:39,510 --> 00:44:41,804
-Get out.
-Young-soo has been

751
00:44:43,013 --> 00:44:44,932
walking on eggshells around you,
hasn't he?

752
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:48,686
I know you're doing this
because you're worried,

753
00:44:48,769 --> 00:44:51,480
but your brother has been overcoming
his hardships

754
00:44:51,563 --> 00:44:53,982
so amazingly that it's unbelievable.

755
00:44:54,066 --> 00:44:56,151
You should admit to his courage
to some degree.

756
00:44:57,069 --> 00:44:58,195
Did you know?

757
00:44:58,946 --> 00:45:01,365
Young-soo had already overcome his injury,

758
00:45:02,741 --> 00:45:05,202
and he has been waiting for you...

759
00:45:06,453 --> 00:45:07,287
this whole time.

760
00:45:34,064 --> 00:45:37,192
GENERAL MANAGER BAEK SEUNG-SOO
OF DREAMS SPARKS A NEW WAVE.

761
00:46:06,096 --> 00:46:07,848
Since when have you been writing it?

762
00:46:12,478 --> 00:46:13,312
It's been a while.

763
00:46:17,274 --> 00:46:18,442
You deceived your family.

764
00:46:18,525 --> 00:46:21,111
I haven't lied about anything
except that I like baseball.

765
00:46:23,030 --> 00:46:24,990
-I worked hard.
-Hey.

766
00:46:25,491 --> 00:46:28,202
I've been telling you to study
so that you can live

767
00:46:28,285 --> 00:46:29,828
-a better life--
-I was sick of baseball

768
00:46:29,912 --> 00:46:31,330
when I was an athlete.

769
00:46:31,914 --> 00:46:33,582
But after this happened to me,

770
00:46:34,583 --> 00:46:36,543
it's become fun watching baseball.

771
00:46:38,378 --> 00:46:40,756
So I was going to tell you last time.

772
00:46:42,049 --> 00:46:43,592
I'm okay with watching baseball now.

773
00:46:44,259 --> 00:46:46,762
-Then why didn't you tell me?
-You threw it all away.

774
00:46:46,845 --> 00:46:48,555
Everything related to baseball.

775
00:46:50,098 --> 00:46:52,684
You always spit at and cursed baseball.

776
00:46:53,519 --> 00:46:55,729
How am I supposed
to tell you that I like it?

777
00:46:59,525 --> 00:47:02,903
-But that's what made you--
-Although you always say so,

778
00:47:02,986 --> 00:47:05,656
you think it happened because of you.

779
00:47:09,660 --> 00:47:11,370
It's been so many years.

780
00:47:12,371 --> 00:47:15,582
Do you think anyone in this country
can hide from baseball?

781
00:47:16,208 --> 00:47:18,418
Then why did you enter a baseball club?

782
00:47:19,253 --> 00:47:22,464
The baseball manager won't let his brother
watch a baseball game.

783
00:47:22,548 --> 00:47:23,841
How hypocritical is that?

784
00:47:24,424 --> 00:47:26,426
Then who would make money?

785
00:47:27,261 --> 00:47:29,263
What can't a man do to make money?

786
00:47:30,222 --> 00:47:32,224
Someone has to make money.

787
00:47:32,307 --> 00:47:34,226
Stop saying that stuff!

788
00:47:35,310 --> 00:47:38,188
Don't you know we live
in a nightmare to watch you

789
00:47:38,272 --> 00:47:40,732
devote your whole life to our family?

790
00:47:41,024 --> 00:47:42,401
I'm the one who can't walk.

791
00:47:42,484 --> 00:47:44,361
Why should you have a sense of guilt,

792
00:47:44,444 --> 00:47:46,363
and why do I have to wait for you?

793
00:47:48,156 --> 00:47:49,616
I'm out of the nightmare.

794
00:47:49,700 --> 00:47:51,785
Why are you still in there looking at me?

795
00:47:52,327 --> 00:47:55,581
"I'll make the sacrifice. You find
a secure job somewhere else."

796
00:47:55,664 --> 00:47:56,707
Isn't that it?

797
00:47:57,833 --> 00:48:00,419
Do you know how suffocating it is
to hear that?

798
00:48:02,921 --> 00:48:05,299
Do I have to be this self-conscious
for all of us to be happy?

799
00:48:05,382 --> 00:48:07,551
Snap out of it already, please!

800
00:48:14,600 --> 00:48:15,684
Fine.

801
00:48:16,518 --> 00:48:19,271
You don't have to hire me.

802
00:48:21,440 --> 00:48:22,983
So let's live a brighter life.

803
00:48:24,902 --> 00:48:26,278
It wasn't your fault.

804
00:48:28,280 --> 00:48:29,489
Do you think...

805
00:48:31,074 --> 00:48:33,827
you'd not be able to blame yourself
if you were me?

806
00:48:34,453 --> 00:48:35,537
Yes.

807
00:48:37,456 --> 00:48:39,207
Because it's really not your fault.

808
00:48:44,963 --> 00:48:47,132
If you were the only one
who was hurt, it'd be different.

809
00:48:48,300 --> 00:48:49,676
But that's not true.

810
00:48:52,220 --> 00:48:53,138
I was...

811
00:48:55,515 --> 00:48:56,433
I was...

812
00:49:19,623 --> 00:49:21,124
We still have to see his progress.

813
00:49:22,084 --> 00:49:24,461
But he has so many bruises on his body.

814
00:49:24,544 --> 00:49:25,754
Do you know what happened?

815
00:49:28,006 --> 00:49:28,966
No.

816
00:49:29,049 --> 00:49:30,592
He's a baseball player, right?

817
00:49:31,843 --> 00:49:33,971
I think there's been physical punishment.

818
00:49:34,137 --> 00:49:37,683
His ankle was severely swollen
where it's not relevant to his injury.

819
00:49:38,892 --> 00:49:41,853
It wouldn't have been easy for him
to run that fast.

820
00:49:55,075 --> 00:49:57,244
MESSAGE INBOX

821
00:50:01,665 --> 00:50:02,916
Young-soo.

822
00:50:03,291 --> 00:50:05,460
Everyone is going through a hard time.

823
00:50:05,711 --> 00:50:07,671
Let's only look forward, okay?

824
00:50:08,255 --> 00:50:09,840
You're the pride of our family.

825
00:50:57,971 --> 00:51:00,390
What are you going to do about the result?

826
00:51:05,520 --> 00:51:07,647
GENERAL MANAGER'S OFFICE

827
00:51:15,614 --> 00:51:16,573
Come in.

828
00:51:23,538 --> 00:51:26,124
DREAMS COME TRUE

829
00:51:36,343 --> 00:51:37,636
Oh, hey.

830
00:51:39,137 --> 00:51:41,098
Why did you suddenly come?
I have classes, too.

831
00:51:41,181 --> 00:51:43,767
I wanted to badmouth someone,

832
00:51:43,850 --> 00:51:45,769
but I couldn't think of anyone else
to do it with.

833
00:51:48,146 --> 00:51:51,608
If that someone is
the frustrating man I'm thinking of,

834
00:51:52,818 --> 00:51:54,820
you've come to the right person.

835
00:52:01,785 --> 00:52:04,496
It was bound to happen one day.

836
00:52:05,413 --> 00:52:09,459
But I think
we put that day off for too long.

837
00:52:11,837 --> 00:52:12,921
I'm okay.

838
00:52:14,840 --> 00:52:15,674
What about you?

839
00:52:17,134 --> 00:52:18,468
Well,

840
00:52:19,636 --> 00:52:22,013
I ended up like this
after putting it off too much.

841
00:52:23,849 --> 00:52:25,934
Unlike Seung-soo and me,

842
00:52:26,017 --> 00:52:28,186
you two are brothers,
so you can't part ways.

843
00:52:28,770 --> 00:52:30,272
Try to overcome it.

844
00:52:33,525 --> 00:52:34,734
I just...

845
00:52:36,486 --> 00:52:37,779
did it for myself.

846
00:52:38,780 --> 00:52:40,031
Right.

847
00:52:40,448 --> 00:52:43,493
Your brother will live
the rest of his life in regret

848
00:52:43,577 --> 00:52:45,996
if he doesn't see us happy.

849
00:52:47,789 --> 00:52:49,749
But aside from that,

850
00:52:50,208 --> 00:52:53,253
you just need to enjoy your life.

851
00:52:55,839 --> 00:52:56,965
And smile a lot.

852
00:53:01,678 --> 00:53:03,054
INCOMING CALL

853
00:53:04,431 --> 00:53:05,390
Hello?

854
00:53:05,473 --> 00:53:09,227
Hello, I'm Lee Se-young of the Dreams.

855
00:53:09,895 --> 00:53:12,063
-Oh, hello.
-Congratulations.

856
00:53:12,147 --> 00:53:13,398
You passed the interview.

857
00:53:14,900 --> 00:53:16,151
Really?

858
00:53:16,902 --> 00:53:17,986
Thank you.

859
00:53:18,069 --> 00:53:20,906
Congratulations once again.

860
00:53:20,989 --> 00:53:22,991
When can you start working?

861
00:53:23,074 --> 00:53:24,951
Right away.

862
00:53:26,203 --> 00:53:28,455
I'll see you tomorrow at work then.

863
00:53:29,080 --> 00:53:31,833
Thank you. Thank you so much.

864
00:53:34,628 --> 00:53:36,338
-Did you get accepted?
-Yes.

865
00:53:37,088 --> 00:53:38,340
-Really?
-Yes!

866
00:53:38,423 --> 00:53:39,466
Goodness.

867
00:53:39,549 --> 00:53:40,926
Congratulations.

868
00:53:41,259 --> 00:53:43,678
-Can you do a good job?
-Of course.

869
00:53:43,762 --> 00:53:44,888
Goodness.

870
00:53:45,305 --> 00:53:47,724
I'm so happy for you.

871
00:53:48,516 --> 00:53:49,601
Good luck.

872
00:53:52,312 --> 00:53:53,438
Mom.

873
00:53:55,523 --> 00:53:57,275
Young-soo is all right now.

874
00:54:01,112 --> 00:54:04,783
I'm fine with everything
as long as he's fine.

875
00:54:08,536 --> 00:54:09,537
Yes.

876
00:54:28,723 --> 00:54:32,352
EXCEPTIONAL, CHALLENGING,
AND PROGRESSIVE BASEBALL

877
00:54:37,607 --> 00:54:40,568
Kyung-min. You're good at your job
because we're related by blood.

878
00:54:41,152 --> 00:54:42,195
You know that, right?

879
00:54:46,658 --> 00:54:48,785
-President Ko.
-Yes, Mr. Kwon?

880
00:54:50,203 --> 00:54:51,788
I need to see Mr. Baek.

881
00:54:52,455 --> 00:54:53,623
May I ask what this is about?

882
00:54:55,375 --> 00:54:57,252
I want to see him. It's been a while.

883
00:55:03,633 --> 00:55:05,510
-Have a seat.
-Okay.

884
00:55:13,560 --> 00:55:15,395
What's the total amount
of last year's salaries?

885
00:55:16,354 --> 00:55:17,981
It's $5,530,000.

886
00:55:19,149 --> 00:55:22,193
We'll need a sharp cut on that.

887
00:55:23,278 --> 00:55:24,863
We can't afford that much money.

888
00:55:35,957 --> 00:55:37,834
What's with the wine between two men?

889
00:55:38,752 --> 00:55:40,962
We're expecting someone,
and he likes wine.

890
00:55:41,046 --> 00:55:42,005
Is someone coming?

891
00:55:42,672 --> 00:55:43,548
It's someone you know.

892
00:55:43,631 --> 00:55:46,134
KWAK HAN-YOUNG, INFIELDER OF THE DREAMS

893
00:55:53,892 --> 00:55:54,768
What's this?

894
00:55:54,851 --> 00:55:56,853
The estimated salary budget of our team.

895
00:55:58,813 --> 00:55:59,898
Why do you have this?

896
00:55:59,981 --> 00:56:01,816
I snuck it out from the operations team.

897
00:56:04,110 --> 00:56:05,570
Do they know about this?

898
00:56:09,074 --> 00:56:12,160
-Can this be leaked?
-You're so fastidious.

899
00:56:13,036 --> 00:56:14,996
Why do you think I'm showing you this?

900
00:56:15,080 --> 00:56:16,206
Look.

901
00:56:17,999 --> 00:56:19,959
I don't want to get involved with this.

902
00:56:22,462 --> 00:56:24,964
-I'll get going.
-Sit down, you punk.

903
00:56:35,225 --> 00:56:37,852
Gosh, what's with this mood?

904
00:56:39,270 --> 00:56:41,231
Sit back down, Mr. Kwak.

905
00:56:48,321 --> 00:56:49,447
Goodness.

906
00:56:51,366 --> 00:56:52,325
You see,

907
00:56:56,579 --> 00:56:58,623
I opened an agency.

908
00:56:59,541 --> 00:57:01,292
I'd like to sign a contract with you

909
00:57:01,376 --> 00:57:03,294
and negotiate your salary.

910
00:57:04,879 --> 00:57:08,258
I don't earn a lot, so you might not
get a lot of commission.

911
00:57:08,341 --> 00:57:11,136
You just need to treat me to a drink.

912
00:57:11,553 --> 00:57:13,930
I'm doing this because I feel bad
for your past contracts.

913
00:57:14,013 --> 00:57:15,640
Right, you punk.

914
00:57:15,890 --> 00:57:18,518
How long will you agree
to what they offer without a say?

915
00:57:21,729 --> 00:57:23,440
Before you,

916
00:57:23,606 --> 00:57:25,733
I've signed contracts with Lee Young-yul,

917
00:57:26,067 --> 00:57:27,777
Jung Tae-soo, and Yoo Min-won.

918
00:57:29,529 --> 00:57:31,739
People at the Dreams look down on me,

919
00:57:32,031 --> 00:57:34,534
but I'm quite renowned outside.

920
00:57:34,617 --> 00:57:36,911
All of them have won a Golden Glove.

921
00:57:38,037 --> 00:57:40,039
Have you signed contracts
with four in total?

922
00:57:40,331 --> 00:57:42,167
Who is the other one?

923
00:57:48,298 --> 00:57:49,924
AGENT CONTRACT

924
00:57:54,971 --> 00:57:57,682
LIM DONG-GYU

925
00:57:58,600 --> 00:58:00,810
Don't tell me you're flustered.

926
00:58:01,311 --> 00:58:02,520
You're Mr. Baek.

927
00:58:03,855 --> 00:58:06,065
Is the topic a little too difficult?

928
00:58:08,026 --> 00:58:08,985
Yes, it is.

929
00:58:10,028 --> 00:58:11,029
Of course,

930
00:58:11,654 --> 00:58:13,406
they might think it's huge

931
00:58:13,490 --> 00:58:15,658
to have their pay cut by 30 percent.

932
00:58:16,409 --> 00:58:19,204
But we'll have to make them understand

933
00:58:19,287 --> 00:58:20,663
our circumstances.

934
00:58:20,747 --> 00:58:23,750
The total of the salary budget
for players has been reduced,

935
00:58:23,833 --> 00:58:25,752
and you want me to negotiate
and sign contracts

936
00:58:25,835 --> 00:58:27,879
with all the players.

937
00:58:28,505 --> 00:58:29,964
Is that it?

938
00:58:30,673 --> 00:58:31,508
Right.

939
00:58:33,259 --> 00:58:35,136
I suggest you make it ten percent.

940
00:58:35,220 --> 00:58:36,930
I told you, it's 30 percent.

941
00:58:38,973 --> 00:58:39,849
Fifteen percent.

942
00:58:39,933 --> 00:58:43,061
Stop talking about money
as if you're bargaining at a market.

943
00:58:43,144 --> 00:58:47,190
It's you who decided on the price
like it's some kind of bargaining.

944
00:58:49,108 --> 00:58:50,902
What are you doing?

945
00:58:52,779 --> 00:58:55,990
How can you make such a decision
without a proper reason?

946
00:58:58,117 --> 00:59:00,745
Do you want me to tell you the reason?

947
00:59:02,372 --> 00:59:03,373
We are...

948
00:59:05,041 --> 00:59:06,000
bad at baseball.

949
00:59:07,460 --> 00:59:08,836
There's more.

950
00:59:08,920 --> 00:59:11,130
We're horrible at baseball.

951
00:59:12,632 --> 00:59:13,925
One more.

952
00:59:14,217 --> 00:59:16,803
We've been horrible at baseball for years.

953
00:59:17,679 --> 00:59:18,638
And one more.

954
00:59:20,056 --> 00:59:23,560
We're suffering a loss from this team.

955
00:59:24,310 --> 00:59:25,186
Right.

956
00:59:26,479 --> 00:59:28,231
We were bad last year and the year before.

957
00:59:28,314 --> 00:59:30,692
That's why our players
have the lowest salaries.

958
00:59:32,151 --> 00:59:34,571
They will hate it
if you cut it down this much.

959
00:59:35,196 --> 00:59:38,324
I wonder why a smart man
would oppose me. Let me tell you this.

960
00:59:39,742 --> 00:59:43,037
It's neither an opinion nor a suggestion.

961
00:59:43,121 --> 00:59:45,582
It's a decision.

962
00:59:47,417 --> 00:59:49,252
And the resolution of our group.

963
01:00:38,968 --> 01:00:42,180
You left work, so get lost to your house.

964
01:00:42,263 --> 01:00:44,223
Why do you want to eat with your superior?

965
01:00:44,307 --> 01:00:47,852
Be grateful
that I'm having a meal with you.

966
01:00:49,145 --> 01:00:50,271
Wait.

967
01:00:52,398 --> 01:00:53,316
What's that?

968
01:00:54,525 --> 01:00:56,027
Is she his girlfriend or wife?

969
01:00:57,945 --> 01:00:58,863
I don't know.

970
01:00:58,946 --> 01:01:02,450
I wondered why he left work
early today, and this was why.

971
01:01:02,533 --> 01:01:04,160
I should ask him about this tomorrow.

972
01:01:04,243 --> 01:01:06,537
Hey, be mature already.

973
01:01:06,621 --> 01:01:08,039
What? What is it this time?

974
01:01:09,290 --> 01:01:11,334
Let's just go.

975
01:01:11,417 --> 01:01:13,670
I didn't know
Mr. Baek could smile like that.

976
01:01:13,753 --> 01:01:15,004
Neither did I.

977
01:01:15,088 --> 01:01:16,297
Let's go.

978
01:01:17,048 --> 01:01:18,049
Okay.

979
01:01:25,556 --> 01:01:27,308
I was supposed to go on a trip today.

980
01:01:28,685 --> 01:01:30,061
Were you?

981
01:01:31,062 --> 01:01:32,689
I canceled it after you called yesterday.

982
01:01:34,273 --> 01:01:37,694
Whether I go with my friend, alone,

983
01:01:38,319 --> 01:01:39,987
or with another man,

984
01:01:41,197 --> 01:01:42,824
I will go on a trip next year.

985
01:01:43,741 --> 01:01:45,451
Let's not see each other
this day next year.

986
01:01:47,704 --> 01:01:48,579
Okay.

987
01:01:50,415 --> 01:01:51,791
It's fine.

988
01:01:54,460 --> 01:01:57,213
If we're obsessed with trying
to comfort one another,

989
01:01:58,589 --> 01:02:01,342
we might never be able
to get over that memory.

990
01:02:02,885 --> 01:02:04,303
That came to my mind.

991
01:02:05,930 --> 01:02:07,849
This day will come every year.

992
01:02:08,725 --> 01:02:10,476
We can't keep doing this.

993
01:02:13,187 --> 01:02:15,398
Let's see each other on other days.

994
01:02:16,232 --> 01:02:17,984
Okay.

995
01:02:20,153 --> 01:02:21,904
Who's going to comfort whom?

996
01:02:23,448 --> 01:02:25,283
We're both strong.

997
01:02:52,268 --> 01:02:53,519
Did you accept that?

998
01:02:53,603 --> 01:02:56,022
Prepare to negotiate fiercely as always.

999
01:02:56,105 --> 01:02:57,148
I've seen many like this.

1000
01:02:57,231 --> 01:02:59,317
People who want to look like
they have principles.

1001
01:02:59,400 --> 01:03:01,027
It's professional, not sandlot baseball.

1002
01:03:01,110 --> 01:03:02,278
We had a drastic cut.

1003
01:03:02,361 --> 01:03:04,447
If you decline this,
I won't offer the same amount.

1004
01:03:04,530 --> 01:03:06,532
We'll evaluate their weaknesses
thoroughly.

1005
01:03:06,616 --> 01:03:08,743
Baek Seung-soo's fake leadership...

1006
01:03:08,826 --> 01:03:11,078
This is the easiest way
to reduce labor costs.

1007
01:03:11,162 --> 01:03:11,996
Expect a backlash.

1008
01:03:12,079 --> 01:03:13,706
He started it by blowing the whistle.

1009
01:03:13,790 --> 01:03:15,458
If he fails, he'll break down.

1010
01:03:15,541 --> 01:03:16,501
Could this be...

1011
01:03:16,584 --> 01:03:18,795
This is the list of ten players
to release from the team.

